{"title":"Storm bow","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Storm_bow","type":"markdown","data":"***Version [0.31](/0.31 \"0.31\")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 \"0.32\") of Crawl.*\n\n|   |                                                                                 |\n| - | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|   | A longbow with the colour of dark rain clouds that fires arrows like lightning. |\n\n[![Longbow storm bow.png](/images/7/7c/Longbow_storm_bow.png)](/File:Longbow_storm_bow.png) ***the +8 storm bow***\n\n+8 [longbow](/Longbow \"Longbow\")\n\n[Electrocution](/Electrocution \"Electrocution\") brand  \n[Penetration](/Penetration \"Penetration\") brand\n\n## Desirability\n\nThe **storm bow**[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1), as a +8 longbow of electrocution, is already a great item for [Ranged Weapons](/Ranged_Weapons \"Ranged Weapons\") users (even if it takes a hefty skill investment). The added penetration allows it to shine in corridors, where only 1 enemy may hit you, but you get to hit multiple enemies for full damage. It also lets you snipe backline enemies without using [Dimensional Bullseye](/Dimensional_Bullseye \"Dimensional Bullseye\"). While a longbow or [triple crossbow](/Triple_crossbow \"Triple crossbow\") of a different brand may be stronger against rElec enemies, the penetration can make this bow worth using as a swapout.\n\n## History\n\n- In [0.24](/0.24 \"0.24\"), the storm bow gained the penetration brand.\n- Prior to [0.23](/0.23 \"0.23\"), the storm bow would occasionally create rain [clouds](/Cloud \"Cloud\") around the wielder, which could turn normal terrain into shallow [water](/Water \"Water\") and shallow water into deep water for up to 100 turns.\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [art-data.txt:780](https://github.com/crawl/crawl/blob/0.31.0/crawl-ref/source/art-data.txt#L780) (0.31.0)\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs